Madam President, I believe that this crisis is an opportunity to move forward firmly and with conviction in creating a strong Europe. In this strong Europe, we will probably have to dispense with the expression ‘improving coordination’, as it means that everything is dependent on the subjects that have to be coordinated and inevitably leads to paralysis and a lack of clarity.
We know that the finances and the public deficits of European countries will suffer until we move towards European financial integration and Eurobonds are issued.
